  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elimelech\u2019s Family Goes to Moab"
      title: "Elimelech\u2019s Family Goes to Moab"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass, in the days when the judges ruled, that there
        was a famine in the land. And a certain man of Bethlehem, Judah, went to
        dwell in the country of Moab, he and his wife and his two sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The name of the man was Elimelech, the name of his wife was Naomi,
        and the names of his two sons were Mahlon and Chilion\u2014Ephrathites of
        Bethlehem, Judah. And they went to the country of Moab and remained there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Elimelech, Naomi\u2019s husband, died; and she was left, and
        her two sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now they took wives of the women of Moab: the name of the one was
        Orpah, and the name of the other Ruth. And they dwelt there about ten years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Naomi Returns with Ruth'
      title: Naomi Returns with Ruth
      number: 5
      content: Then both Mahlon and Chilion also died; so the woman survived her
        two sons and her husband.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then she arose with her daughters-in-law that she might return from
        the country of Moab, for she had heard in the country of Moab that the Lord
        had visited His people by giving them bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore she went out from the place where she was, and her two
        daughters-in-law with her; and they went on the way to return to the land
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, \u201CGo, return each
        to her mother\u2019s house. The Lord deal kindly with you, as you have dealt
        with the dead and with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Lord grant that you may find rest, each in the house of her husband.\u201DSo
        she kissed them, and they lifted up their voices and wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they said to her, \u201CSurely we will return with you to your
        people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Naomi said, \u201CTurn back, my daughters; why will you go with
        me? Are there still sons in my womb, that they may be your husbands? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Turn back, my daughters, go\u2014for I am too old to have a husband.
        If I should say I have hope, if I should have a husband tonight and should
        also bear sons, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "would you wait for them till they were grown? Would you restrain
        yourselves from having husbands? No, my daughters; for it grieves me very
        much for your sakes that the hand of the Lord has gone out against me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Then they lifted up their voices and wept again; and Orpah kissed
        her mother-in-law, but Ruth clung to her.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And she said, \u201CLook, your sister-in-law has gone back to her
        people and to her gods; return after your sister-in-law.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Ruth said:\u201CEntreat me not to leave you,Or  to turn back
        from following after you;For wherever you go, I will go;And wherever you
        lodge, I will lodge;Your people shall  be my people,And your God, my God."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Where you die, I will die,And there will I be buried.The Lord do
        so to me, and more also,If anything  but death parts you and me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: When she saw that she was determined to go with her, she stopped speaking
        to her.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now the two of them went until they came to Bethlehem. And it happened,
        when they had come to Bethlehem, that all the city was excited because of
        them; and the women said, \u201CIs this Naomi?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But she said to them, \u201CDo not call me Naomi; call me Mara, for
        the Almighty has dealt very bitterly with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I went out full, and the Lord has brought me home again empty. Why
        do you call me Naomi, since the Lord has testified against me, and the Almighty
        has afflicted me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So Naomi returned, and Ruth the Moabitess her daughter-in-law with
        her, who returned from the country of Moab. Now they came to Bethlehem at
        the beginning of barley harvest.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ruth Meets Boaz'
      title: Ruth Meets Boaz
      number: 1
      content: "There was a relative of Naomi\u2019s husband, a man of great wealth,
        of the family of Elimelech. His name was  Boaz. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Ruth the Moabitess said to Naomi, \u201CPlease let me go to the
        field, and glean heads of grain after him in whose sight I may find favor.\u201DAnd
        she said to her, \u201CGo, my daughter.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Then she left, and went and gleaned in the field after the reapers.
        And she happened to come to the part of the field belonging to Boaz, who
        was of the family of Elimelech.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now behold, Boaz came from Bethlehem, and said to the reapers, \u201CThe
        Lord  be with you!\u201DAnd they answered him, \u201CThe Lord bless you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Boaz said to his servant who was in charge of the reapers, \u201CWhose
        young woman is this?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the servant who was in charge of the reapers answered and said,
        \u201CIt is the young Moabite woman who came back with Naomi from the country
        of Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And she said, \u2018Please let me glean and gather after the reapers
        among the sheaves.\u2019 So she came and has continued from morning until
        now, though she rested a little in the house.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Boaz said to Ruth, \u201CYou will listen, my daughter, will
        you not? Do not go to glean in another field, nor go from here, but stay
        close by my young women. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Let your eyes be on the field which they reap, and go after them.
        Have I not commanded the young men not to touch you? And when you are thirsty,
        go to the vessels and drink from what the young men have drawn.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So she fell on her face, bowed down to the ground, and said to him,
        \u201CWhy have I found favor in your eyes, that you should take notice of
        me, since I am a foreigner?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Boaz answered and said to her, \u201CIt has been fully reported
        to me, all that you have done for your mother-in-law since the death of your
        husband, and how you have left your father and your mother and the land of
        your birth, and have come to a people whom you did not know before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The Lord repay your work, and a full reward be given you by the Lord
        God of Israel, under whose wings you have come for refuge.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then she said, \u201CLet me find favor in your sight, my lord; for
        you have comforted me, and have spoken kindly to your maidservant, though
        I am not like one of your maidservants.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now Boaz said to her at mealtime, \u201CCome here, and eat of the
        bread, and dip your piece of bread in the vinegar.\u201D So she sat beside
        the reapers, and he passed parched grain to her; and she ate and was satisfied,
        and kept some back. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when she rose up to glean, Boaz commanded his young men, saying,
        \u201CLet her glean even among the sheaves, and do not reproach her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Also let grain from the bundles fall purposely for her; leave it
        that she may glean, and do not rebuke her.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So she gleaned in the field until evening, and beat out what she
        had gleaned, and it was about an ephah of barley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Then she took it up and went into the city, and her mother-in-law
        saw what she had gleaned.So she brought out and gave to her what she had
        kept back after she had been satisfied.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And her mother-in-law said to her, \u201CWhere have you gleaned today?
        And where did you work? Blessed be the one who took notice of you.\u201DSo
        she told her mother-in-law with whom she had worked, and said, \u201CThe
        man\u2019s name with whom I worked today is Boaz.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Naomi said to her daughter-in-law, \u201CBlessed be he of the
        Lord, who has not forsaken His kindness to the living and the dead!\u201D
        And Naomi said to her, \u201CThis man is a relation of ours, one of our close
        relatives.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Ruth the Moabitess said, \u201CHe also said to me, \u2018You shall
        stay close by my young men until they have finished all my harvest.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Naomi said to Ruth her daughter-in-law, \u201CIt  is good, my
        daughter, that you go out with his young women, and that people do not meet
        you in any other field.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So she stayed close by the young women of Boaz, to glean until the
        end of barley harvest and wheat harvest; and she dwelt with her mother-in-law.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ruth\u2019s Redemption Assured"
      title: "Ruth\u2019s Redemption Assured"
      number: 1
      content: "Then Naomi her mother-in-law said to her, \u201CMy daughter, shall
        I not seek security for you, that it may be well with you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now Boaz, whose young women you were with, is  he not our relative?
        In fact, he is winnowing barley tonight at the threshing floor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore wash yourself and anoint yourself, put on your best garment
        and go down to the threshing floor; but do not make yourself known to the
        man until he has finished eating and drinking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then it shall be, when he lies down, that you shall notice the place
        where he lies; and you shall go in, uncover his feet, and lie down; and he
        will tell you what you should do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And she said to her, \u201CAll that you say to me I will do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So she went down to the threshing floor and did according to all
        that her mother-in-law instructed her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And after Boaz had eaten and drunk, and his heart was cheerful, he
        went to lie down at the end of the heap of grain; and she came softly, uncovered
        his feet, and lay down.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now it happened at midnight that the man was startled, and turned
        himself; and there, a woman was lying at his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said, \u201CWho are you?\u201DSo she answered, \u201CI am
        Ruth, your maidservant. Take your maidservant under your wing, for you are
        a close relative.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBlessed are you of the Lord, my daughter! For
        you have shown more kindness at the end than at the beginning, in that you
        did not go after young men, whether poor or rich. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And now, my daughter, do not fear. I will do for you all that you
        request, for all the people of my town know that you are a virtuous woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now it is true that I am a close relative; however, there is a relative
        closer than I. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Stay this night, and in the morning it shall be that if he will perform
        the duty of a close relative for you\u2014good; let him do it. But if he
        does not want to perform the duty for you, then I will perform the duty for
        you, as the Lord lives! Lie down until morning.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So she lay at his feet until morning, and she arose before one could
        recognize another. Then he said, \u201CDo not let it be known that the woman
        came to the threshing floor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Also he said, \u201CBring the shawl that is on you and hold it.\u201D
        And when she held it, he measured six ephahs of barley, and laid it on her.
        Then she went into the city."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When she came to her mother-in-law, she said, \u201CIs that you,
        my daughter?\u201DThen she told her all that the man had done for her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And she said, \u201CThese six ephahs of barley he gave me; for he
        said to me, \u2018Do not go empty-handed to your mother-in-law.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then she said, \u201CSit still, my daughter, until you know how the
        matter will turn out; for the man will not rest until he has concluded the
        matter this day.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Boaz Redeems Ruth'
      title: Boaz Redeems Ruth
      number: 1
      content: "Now Boaz went up to the gate and sat down there; and behold, the
        close relative of whom Boaz had spoken came by. So Boaz said, \u201CCome
        aside, friend, sit down here.\u201D So he came aside and sat down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he took ten men of the elders of the city, and said, \u201CSit
        down here.\u201D So they sat down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said to the close relative, \u201CNaomi, who has come back
        from the country of Moab, sold the piece of land which belonged to our brother
        Elimelech. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I thought to inform you, saying, \u2018Buy it back in the presence
        of the inhabitants and the elders of my people. If you will redeem it, redeem
        it; but if you will not redeem it, then tell me, that I may know; for there 
        is no one but you to redeem it, and I am next after you.\u2019 \u201DAnd
        he said, \u201CI will redeem it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Boaz said, \u201COn the day you buy the field from the hand
        of Naomi, you must also buy it from Ruth the Moabitess, the wife of the dead,
        to perpetuate the name of the dead through his inheritance.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the close relative said, \u201CI cannot redeem it for myself,
        lest I ruin my own inheritance. You redeem my right of redemption for yourself,
        for I cannot redeem it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now this was  the  custom in former times in Israel concerning redeeming
        and exchanging, to confirm anything: one man took off his sandal and gave
        it to the other, and this was a confirmation in Israel.'
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore the close relative said to Boaz, \u201CBuy it for yourself.\u201D
        So he took off his sandal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Boaz said to the elders and all the people, \u201CYou are witnesses
        this day that I have bought all that was Elimelech\u2019s, and all that was
        Chilion\u2019s and Mahlon\u2019s, from the hand of Naomi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Moreover, Ruth the Moabitess, the widow of Mahlon, I have acquired
        as my wife, to perpetuate the name of the dead through his inheritance, that
        the name of the dead may not be cut off from among his brethren and from
        his position at the gate. You are witnesses this day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And all the people who were at the gate, and the elders, said, \u201CWe 
        are witnesses. The Lord make the woman who is coming to your house like Rachel
        and Leah, the two who built the house of Israel; and may you prosper in Ephrathah
        and be famous in Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Descendants of Boaz and Ruth'
      title: Descendants of Boaz and Ruth
      number: 12
      content: "May your house be like the house of Perez, whom Tamar bore to Judah,
        because of the offspring which the Lord will give you from this young woman.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Boaz took Ruth and she became his wife; and when he went in to
        her, the Lord gave her conception, and she bore a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the women said to Naomi, \u201CBlessed be the Lord, who has
        not left you this day without a close relative; and may his name be famous
        in Israel! "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And may he be to you a restorer of life and a nourisher of your old
        age; for your daughter-in-law, who loves you, who is better to you than seven
        sons, has borne him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Naomi took the child and laid him on her bosom, and became a
        nurse to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Also the neighbor women gave him a name, saying, \u201CThere is a
        son born to Naomi.\u201D And they called his name Obed. He is the father
        of Jesse, the father of David."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now this is the genealogy of Perez: Perez begot Hezron; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hezron begot Ram, and Ram begot Amminadab; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Amminadab begot Nahshon, and Nahshon begot Salmon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Salmon begot Boaz, and Boaz begot Obed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Obed begot Jesse, and Jesse begot David.
      comments: []
